Fires burn thousands of acres in seven western states, at times
threatening homes, as firefighters contend with wind and high
temperatures.  The Boise Interagency Fire Center in Idaho listed 7,000
to 7,500 people fighting fires throughout the U.S., along with 42 air
tankers, 14 guide planes and 10 helicopters.  So far this year, the
agency has reported 31,000 fires, which have burned 1,117,000 acres.
In the same period last year, it had 54,000 fires which burned 765,000
acres. To date, the largest fire in the lower 48 states is the Diamond
Peak Utah fire, which burned 12,200 acres.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d22"
TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
DOCREF="AP890714-0129"
