Rain and higher humidity helped firefighters control blazes in six
western states.  Firefighters in Nebraska began seeding grass and
planting trees.  However, the return of hot and dry weather will soon
end this welcomed break.  In New Mexico, a lightening- caused fire
polluted a creek with ash.  Biologists there rescued hundreds of the
endangered species of Gila trout.  566 trout were caught with
long-handled nets and taken to the Mescalero Fish Hatchery, where they
will remain until the creek becomes ash free.  Officials hope at least
90% will survive.  Elsewhere, an arson-caused fire blackened much of
California's scenic coastline near Big Sur.</SUM>
